{"name":"Mounted Combatant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character has a knack for getting the best out of his mount.</p>\n<p>They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll, and may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for any mount they are riding or command, using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} skill instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}. Each success and raise negates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, he may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} to spur his mount to greater speeds. With success, the mount gains +2 Pace for this round. a failure causes the mount to gain no increase to its Pace and it suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} due to the exertion.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"00pjVozNtCcqmrOt"}
{"name":"Berserk","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Berserkers become wild and nearly uncontrollable when the &ldquo;red rage&rdquo; takes them, but they are deadly killing machines as well! </span></p>\n<p>Immediately after suffering a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound or a Shaken} result (from physical damage only), your hero must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll or go Berserk. She </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">can </span>voluntarily fail this check if she likes.<br /></span></p>\n<p>Going Berserk has the following effects:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fury:</strong>&nbsp; The character&rsquo;s Strength increases a die type and every melee attack must be a </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attack}</span></strong>. She cannot use any skills that require wit or concentration (GM&rsquo;s call). She may scream out threats and use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, for example.</span> &nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Enraged:&nbsp; </strong>She ignores one level of Wound penalties (this stacks with any other abilities that reduce Wound penalties).</span> &nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Reckless Abandon:</strong>&nbsp; Anytime a berserker rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} check, she hits a random target within range of her attack (</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">not </span>the intended target), friend or foe. If there are no applicable targets, the blow simply misses, smashes nearby objects, etc.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>After five consecutive rounds of berserk fury, the hero takes a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}. At ten rounds, she takes another level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}&nbsp;and the rage ends. She may also </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">choose </span>to end her rage at any time by making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &ndash;2 roll (as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}; possibly avoiding @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}&nbsp;if she manages to end her rage before it&rsquo;s incurred!). Start the count anew if she goes berserk again, even in the same battle.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"07pmfI2aXgxIwpMH"}
{"name":"Arcane Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>True understanding of magical energy comes with practice and experience. Wizards who take this Edge gain access to all their powers&rsquo; Epic Power Modifiers (see the Powers Chapter).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wizard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0JljpEm1qwB5lG6b"}
{"name":"Assassin III","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Assassin II"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0UyqdvfkhhN9SRkw"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Divine Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, a character gains one die type in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Divine Magic)]{Arcane Background (Divine Magic)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0mglDyjieIGqbDQL"}
{"name":"Bard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The bards of Eberron bring epic tales of heroism and tragedy to the people. Many are renowned far and wide for their talents, but few realize how crucial they are to parties of brave adventurers. They bolster their allies in dire circumstances, beguile their enemies, and often battle evil with a sword in one hand and a lute in the other.</p>\n<p>Bards cast spells by singing, playing an instrument, reciting poetry, or reciting epic tales. They are usually erudite individuals, traveling the land to learn bawdy songs, great histories, and epic legends.</p>\n<p>Allies must be able to hear the bard to benefit from his various abilities.</p>\n<p>Bards gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Bard Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Performance d4+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"16UCUpAsIwqEfxVY"}
{"name":"Druid","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Within the purity of the elements and the order of the wilds lingers a power beyond the marvels of civilization. Furtive yet undeniable, these primal magics are guarded by servants of philosophical balance known as druids. Allies to beasts and manipulators of nature, these protectors of the wild strive to shield their lands from all who would threaten them.</p>\n<p>Rewarded for their devotion with incredible powers, druids gain unparalleled shapeshifting abilities, the companionship of mighty beasts, and the power to call upon nature&rsquo;s wrath. The mightiest temper powers akin to storms, earthquakes, and volcanoes with wisdom long forgotten by civilization.</p>\n<p>Druids gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid Armor Interference (Light)]{Druid Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druidic Vow]{Druidic Vow}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Bond]{Nature Bond}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Sense]{Nature Sense}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wilderness Stride (Druid)]{Wilderness Stride}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Survival d6+, Faith d4+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1OLvUECuwtNl6npZ"}
{"name":"Extreme Explorer III","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Extreme Explorer II"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1WcdGPgT5qh9aDEr"}
{"name":"Wholeness of Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The monk may spend one of his Mystic Powers Power Points to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll}. This does not count as spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Monk"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7kugpblr0yu","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Monk","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1rPlmpu19uTcrdbp"}
{"name":"Improved Sweep","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Sweep allows a character to make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with a two-handed weapon and apply it against all targets in his Reach (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that&rsquo;s hit.</p>\n<p>A character or creature may only perform a Sweep once per turn. Sweep may not be combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} in the same action.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Some creatures have the Sweep Edge even though they don't have two-handed weapons. In their case their size, lanky limbs, or other advantages allow them to make Sweep attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sweep"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"22UFqCzmFzddB41S"}
{"name":"Sweep","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Sweep allows a character to make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with a two-handed weapon and apply it against all targets in his Reach at a &minus;2 penalty (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that&rsquo;s hit.</p>\n<p>A character or creature may only perform a Sweep once per turn. Sweep may not be combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} in the same action.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Some creatures have the Sweep Edge even though they don't have two-handed weapons. In their case their size, lanky limbs, or other advantages allow them to make Sweep attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2U9vqShcXp8Uosfh"}
{"name":"Destroy Undead","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}, the cleric spends 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to channel positive energy in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on herself. Every undead creature within the template must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll or take a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (this may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soaked} as usual).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Cleric"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rzst3tdjv7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Cleric","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2XJNC2IpBqS9rmRm"}
{"name":"Loremaster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A gatherer of secrets and arcane lore, this character values the acquisition of intellectual might above all else. Often obsessed by the written word, the loremaster believes knowledge is power.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore: </strong>She gets a free reroll when making @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Arcana or Common Knowledge or Lore d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2eu2ww0Ur9A55mXP"}
{"name":"Disciple of Kol Korran","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3JV2QBGzdf0JWPsE"}
{"name":"Mark of Warding","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane protection}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{glyph}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{sentry}</em>.</span></p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.&nbsp; She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>The Mark of Warding doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with the Mark of Warding (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dwarf"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m9rojhhzc3m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4MkKTYCQxkOHOqUB"}
{"name":"Rogue","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4OPPHqozwiuqhQXa"}
{"name":"Disciple of Dol Arrah","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dol Arrah]{Dol Arrah} disciples treat his character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} as being one higher for the purposes of taking Combat Edges. He must meet all other requirements as normal.</p>\n<p>In addition, they gain +2 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls to detect hidden objects or creatures, including those under an <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibilty]{Invisibilty} </em>spell. Against foes cloaked in such a manner, they halve penalties to hit them (once they have detected them).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Divine Magic), Faith d8+, Fighting d8+, Notice d6+, follower of Dol Dorn"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4hVuU9lkIJUi1KDN"}
{"name":"Combat Prowess","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>2</p>\n<p>While most stories about heroes start of close to the truth, they quickly spiral out of control, attributing heroes with abilities far in excess of what they actually possessed.</p>\n<p>The character may take a Combat Edge immediately. He must meet all the requirements as normal.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"40+ Glory"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4rrMCKxI9Bab3xMv"}
{"name":"Improved Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Improved Enchant works the same way as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant]{Enchant} with one important exception--the power is \"always on\" and no longer requires @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to use (it has infinite points). The cost, however, is 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} required to activate the power.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Enchanting a sword with Smite would require 2000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When the device is created, the creator makes an arcane skill roll. Failure means the Eberron Dragonshards are lost (and at the GM's fiat, the device is destroyed as well--or it could become cursed). A success means the power is activated as usual. A raise means the power forever activates with a raise (if desired by the user).</p>\n<p>Artifacts which are always on (a ring of invisibility, a cloak of stealth, and so on), don't require an arcane skill roll to activate&mdash;but may require an action to \"ready\"&mdash;the ring must be put on, the cloak pulled over the shoulder, etc. Thus a ring of invisibility could always be worn and require no activation roll&mdash;but the wearer would always be invisible.</p>\n<p>Artifacts requiring activation, such as a wand of fireballs, require a suitable skill roll (Shooting for wands, for example). All artifacts created using this Edge are called major artifacts.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Enchant"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_86id21xaqgr","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4uvdiZD09RHUWwSJ"}
{"name":"Advanced Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You gain the additional ability listed for your @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bloodlines]{bloodline}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Sorcerer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cna61w56xkj","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Sorcerer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5XyWAoeGy6rjykK6"}
{"name":"Disciple of Dol Dorn","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":null,"notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Miracles), Agility or Strength d8+, Faith d8+, Fighting d8+, follower of Dol Dorn"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5nvjWhemvJvnoXGz"}
{"name":"Channel Energy","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Clerics can cast the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power at a Range of Spirit rather than Touch. Their&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em>&nbsp;power also has the Additional Recipients Power Modifier, allowing them to heal nearby allies at the cost of one extra Power Point each.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Cleric"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rzst3tdjv7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Cleric","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"67Ym1lAt1RiOGjOa"}
{"name":"Master of Artifice","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some artificers can build incredible devices out of most anything.</p>\n<p>A master artificer can spend up to three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to &ldquo;jury rig&rdquo; an infused device from any reasonable collection of spare partsm, this must include some @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonshards]{Eberron dragonshard residum} equal to 50 gp per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} of the power used. This allows her to activate any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{power} of her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or lower, with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} cost of 3 or lower.</p>\n<p>The total cost of an individual power (plus any modifiers) cannot exceed the points spent to create it, nor can the artificer apply @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitations} to the infused device. She may attempt to create multiple devices as long as she has the points to do so.</p>\n<p>Each infused device is created and activated with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll at &ndash;2. This takes one entire turn, during which she can do nothing else (she cannot take @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions} that turn). In all other ways, it works as the normal activation of a power.</p>\n<p>The inventor uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} directly from her pool for the device, but once its initial @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} is finished (it cannot be maintained) it falls apart into its component pieces.</p>\n<h2 class=\"blue-example\">Example</h2>\n<p>Tristam wants to use<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> to help Red fight a chimera, but only has the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast} </em>powers. Fortunately, he's a Master of Artifice, so Tristam can put <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait} </em> into an \"girdle of ogre strength\" The device can take up to three points worth of powers, so he adds the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hinder or Hurry (+1)]{Hurry} modifier and gives Red +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} as well</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Artificer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6C4mhgDENRT8kjbF"}
{"name":"Trap Sense","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Rogue"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6DR27hhjIZlU50Vr"}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Close fighters train to go for vital areas and weak spots for quick and lethal kills. The attacker adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll equal to his enemy's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6INEEW3jMc6taMbM"}
{"name":"Death before Dishonor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character has led his army to many victories, and the men have come to accept retreat as a stain on their honor.</p>\n<p>The character gains +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls when rolling for Morale in a Mass Battle.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hold the Line, Spirit d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6OkG1no2qx4eYdD3"}
{"name":"University Trained","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You attended one of the prestigious universities in the world. You like to read, and you absorb the information like a sponge. These books can be found in classrooms, in libraries or even in the local coffee shop. Book Learning confers 4 additional skill points on the Character, but these points must be spent on the following: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} </em>or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science}.</p>\n<p>Because of your interest in books, a character with this Edge gains one additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language} at a d4.</p>\n<p><strong>Special: </strong>This Edge must be taken during character creation or after actually going to one of the schools of Khorvaire with DM approval.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7N6BWKFSb15QvmhQ"}
{"name":"Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Sorcery requires rapid, intricate, and unhindered somatic movements. Sorcerers subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} rolls&nbsp;and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls&nbsp;when wearing light, medium, or heavy armor, or using light, medium, or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cna61w56xkj","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Sorcerer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7q5cDMtNZFFtcc3x"}
{"name":"Favored Terrain","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Choose a terrain type (Arctic, Desert, Forest, Jungle, Plains, Hills/ Mountains, Rivers/Seas, Swamp, Urban, or Underground). The ranger draws an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} for initiative when in his Favored Terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y4rfdvvjk7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Ranger","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8GNCuH8upI5vaO78"}
{"name":"Wilderness Stride (Druid)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Druids pass through rough terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore movement penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} in these kinds of terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8SGDFQeWKFGuzUF6"}
{"name":"Favored Powers (Wizard)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The wizard has great familiarity with certain powers and can cast them quickly and easily. Once per turn, he may ignore up to two points of any penalties (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, etc.) when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em>.</p>\n<p>This Edge doesn&rsquo;t give him those powers&mdash; they must be taken separately.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wizard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8Yo1PiS3hNFjWK80"}
{"name":"Wizard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Beyond the veil of the mundane hide the secrets of absolute power. Legends, mysteries, and wonders of arcane realms call to those with the ambition&mdash;and the intellect&mdash;to rise above the common folk to grasp true might. Such is the path of the wizard.</p>\n<p>These shrewd magic-users research, collect, and covet esoteric knowledge. Some choose to become a master of a particular field of magical study. Others embrace versatility, reveling in the unbounded wonders of all magic. In either case, wizards prove a cunning and potent lot, capable of smiting their foes, empowering their allies, and shaping the world to their every desire.</p>\n<p>Wizards have the following abilities.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Bond]{Arcane Bond}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Schools]{Schools}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spellbooks]{Spellbooks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard Armor Interference&nbsp;(Cloth)]{Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8Zk4gEgRK2okPuVT"}
{"name":"Loremaster II","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Loremaster"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8celTZDklI4dclmH"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Flame","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9XOk5sDTTceMLQHm"}
{"name":"Drop!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a ranged weapon targets an ally within the hero's command radius, the character may order him to drop to the ground. This allows the intended target to fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn, even if he has acted already, gaining the benefits of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Medium Cover}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AAYChro2WyiM02QS"}
{"name":"Artificer Armor Restriction (Medium)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The casting of artifice infusions requires freedom of movement. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} skill rolls when wearing heavy armor or using a heavy shield.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AQk9BwXONnJeh3tU"}
{"name":"Born in Battle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good grasp of terrain and tactics, as well as knowledge of military history and enemy forces, can bring a general victory even when his troops are inferior to his enemy&rsquo;s. The character gets +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls. In addition, he gains a +2 bonus to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ag0egCcGbHDtQHPL"}
{"name":"Bard Armor Interference (Light)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bulky armor interferes with a bard&rsquo;s grace and dexterity. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} rolls and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AgYIRBICmVao9aLG"}
{"name":"Unarmed Strike","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Monks cause Str+d4 damage with their hands, feet, or other @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons} (if inhuman and have such appendages).</p>\n<p>If the monk already has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage die from Claws (available to some races), or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edge, increase the damage a die type for each.</p>\n<p>Monks can apply the benefit of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon} Edge to their unarmed attacks.</p>\n<p>Monks always count as armed. Some use regular weapons in their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{off-hand}, but abilities that refer to their Unarmed Strike apply only to unarmed attacks as defined above.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Barbarian"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7kugpblr0yu","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Monk","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AsIWfYEk71ubHLnp"}
{"name":"Martial Prowess","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The fighter gets a free reroll on any failed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Fighter"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cbe5u35c01","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Fighter","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"B7NEfDEU6WdYnU7m"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Sorcerer)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_cna61w56xkj","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Sorcerer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BGZEXB6ts2reemxD"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to intercept blows meant for others. At the start of his turn the character may nominate one adjacent ally. So long as the ally remains adjacent, the ally uses the hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} in place of his own. This benefit is immediately lost if the parrying character is rendered incapable of parrying a blow.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Agility d8, Block, Notice d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BMo80eL5WWdnPzpN"}
{"name":"Formation Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character has trained to fight alongside others, overwhelming their common foe with synchronized strikes and blows. She adds +2 to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus instead of +1. The maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up}&nbsp;bonus is still +4 no matter how many Formation Fighters stand together.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BXeIw40ISynTCheL"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, a character gains one die type in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BZ1zUpLgsGiUhEDe"}
{"name":"Mercy","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As an action, a paladin can grant &ldquo;Mercy&rdquo; to any character within a Range equal to her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. Mercy can automatically remove one of the following states: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Paladin"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BhQ29shbDnAUZyYy"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BsSj2cVy1kQT6cEq"}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Monk)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action, the monk can invoke one of the following \"ki\" powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>&nbsp;and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>. All are self only, but the monk gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The monk has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the monk also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Monk"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7kugpblr0yu","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Monk","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ByhYQ9dff7DjSt0P"}
{"name":"True Berserker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some warriors nurture the rage inside them, learning to call upon it almost at will. A True Berserker may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge at any time.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands, Dark Ages</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Berserk, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"C3OCKjFrhmul1PTu"}
{"name":"Craft Arcane Device","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those who tangle with supernatural forces sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a magic sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even bless holy relics with divine grace.</p>\n<p>The hero can create <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}</strong> and give them to their allies. Where possible, the device reflects the forger&rsquo;s background. A bard&rsquo;s Arcane Devices are works of art, such as a singing sword, a magical instrument, an epic poem, etc.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Repair d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qafe4ipyce","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CSmgLtT7cWw3ypMH"}
