{"name":"Assassin","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those with this Edge are adept at infiltration and cold, efficient murder. They consider themselves artisans, and their medium is death.</p>\n<p><strong>Death Attack:</strong> If the assassin strikes a living victim with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} and causes at least one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (after any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soaking}), the foe must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll or die.</p>\n<p>If the assassin @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} or slays a victim he had @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on, the victim drops quietly and without a sound. It may even be a few moments before those nearby notice the situation, depending on the circumstances.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Sneak Attack ability"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DEIgNcxLcZtUg7dS"}
{"name":"Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The sorcerer must choose a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bloodlines]{bloodline}. Beneath each Bloodline description is also the additional special ability one gains when taking the Advanced Bloodline Edge.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sorcerer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cna61w56xkj","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Sorcerer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DecaLdVt7Bop7HTR"}
{"name":"Nature Sense","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Druids commune with nature and its spirits. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} is linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rather than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DhZHcNEWg2EoaKgn"}
{"name":"Improved Giant Killer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero may choose to ignore the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} of a creature three sizes or more than them. This Edge does not work with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area effect attacks}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Giant Killer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DutP5j6qLMgJoYuu"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Bard)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Dvbw47Du8SPf7rQg"}
{"name":"Intimidating Glare","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The fearsome and baleful gaze of the wild barbarian unsettles all but the stoutest souls.</span></p>\n<p>When the barbarian&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} is a Jack or higher, she may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll as a limited free action. She also ignores the usual advice on Repetition. She may issue threats and insults if she wants, but her terrible glare is often enough to send shivers down her foes' spines.</span> </p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Barbarian"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_uz53jzntey","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Barbarian","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"E3W0lMHG8acPzi5B"}
{"name":"Spellbooks","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wizard spells are strange, complex things that fade quickly from the minds of even the most accomplished casters. For this reason, each wizard maintains a spellbook with the spells he&rsquo;s translated and acquired. He studies them daily, transcribing their mystical patterns onto his mind.</p>\n<p>The link to the book is far more than rote memorization&mdash;it is an arcane bond with the power and patterns within. If a wizard doesn&rsquo;t have access to his spellbook, he may continue to cast normally until the next sunset or sunrise (whichever comes first). After that, the magical imprint on his mind fades and he can no longer cast them.</p>\n<p>Wizards may only carry one active spellbook at a time. The mountains of scrolls, magical notations, and research needed to prepare another cannot be carried with the wizard and must be stored safely somewhere. It takes a week of work and 500 gp to create a replacement spellbook once the wizard has access to his magical notes.</p>\n<p>When a wizard finds a new spellbook or scroll, the spells it contains become available as choices to the wizard when he next chooses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers} Edge. Moreover, a wizard taking the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}&nbsp;Edge can learn a third new power, if all the new powers are learned from scrolls and spellbooks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ECdujFH2Ltpv1xeK"}
{"name":"Wilderness Stride (Ranger)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rangers pass through rough terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore movement penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} through these types of terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y4rfdvvjk7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Ranger","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EHMLibL8lXHc9fiE"}
