{"name":"House Scion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into the privilege of a dragonmarked house or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich} Edge), but she still walks in the elite circles of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonmarks]{dragonmarked houses}.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to take on the name of their house for a last name, denoting being a scion of the house.</p>\n<p>House scions add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with other house members. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the information about what is going on within their house, recognize family names or members of their house, or recall gossip concerning others within their house.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FvLb2IDixg05Sdlp"}
{"name":"Great Ki","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The monk further nurtures and refines his ki. He adds the following spells to his Mystic Powers Edge:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em>&nbsp;(Strength),&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{wall walker}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Monk, Mystic Powers (Monk)"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7kugpblr0yu","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Monk","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"G2OS9rHMmg9MODUD"}
{"name":"Fanaticism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is most appropriate for members of the military, but the leader of a seasoned band of monster hunters might develop it as well.</p>\n<p>Troops under command of a character with this Edge add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fervor"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"G9ofsDIOAAfNuQOE"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Leadership Edges","children":["ddMKqrusPvUvxNjw","tIg9wafAMFaBbkk9","Ag0egCcGbHDtQHPL","oeFPsr0Pz9Rzll7P","SYBOPeq6ZJ6hhLvO","6OkG1no2qx4eYdD3","AAYChro2WyiM02QS","G9ofsDIOAAfNuQOE","QqZ4H2um3PjL4jqK","dRuV7EijZViqdXkr","jrXQ1LZa4ioCHlrv","HJtbH3ZeMXNqHHnA"],"folderPath":["temp_eh5365j3hoj"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"GR1uC607xzGNR1dV"}
{"name":"Adaptable Caster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Magic is varied and wonderful, and wizards are exposed to countless tomes, scrolls, and incantations as they master their craft. Sometimes they use this knowledge to recall variations of their various enchantments. </span></p>\n<p>A Wizard can spend 1 extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} when casting a power to change its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}. A fireball (<em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blast]{blast}</em></span>) might manifest as a lightning bolt, for example. This can often have important consequences if a foe has a particular resistance or weakness to the spell&rsquo;s usual Trapping</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Artificer, Magic, or Wizard), arcane skill d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qafe4ipyce","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GjpXPVBp5QI7ueWz"}
{"name":"Followers","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>10</p>\n<p>Famous heroes attract entourages and hangers-on. The hero gains the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Followers]{Followers} Edge regardless of his character Rank. The GM and player should work together to determine the nature of the Followers, based on the character&rsquo;s profession and deeds.</p>\n<p>Followers are not automatically replaced when they die. Additional Followers may be gained at Legendary as normal through taking the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Followers]{Followers} Edge with advances or by earning more Glory and taking this benefit.</p>\n<p>Followers don&rsquo;t automatically leave if a character&rsquo;s Glory drops below the level he gained this benefit, but they begin to grumble, refuse orders, and eventually mutiny. In game terms, the character&rsquo;s Leadership Edges no longer work on them. When his Glory rises above the threshold again, his Followers stop grumbling.</p>\n<p>As noted previously in this chapter, having Extras accompany you on every mission means you have to slay more foes to earn Glory.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"40+ Glory"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Gmo1wALTBCm1xpBU"}
{"name":"Eldritch Knight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Elite warriors who train in both the martial and arcane arts learn how to take extra advantage of their prowess in both. These versatile heroes, the Eldritch Knights, are usually characters who studied both the martial and arcane arts.</p>\n<p><strong>Eldritch Recharge:</strong> Anytime the knight gets a raise on a damaging attack roll (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, or arcane skill), he regains a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HIcXvBpB7DoomiO3"}
{"name":"Siege Mentality","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character has a strong defensive mentality and understands how to make the most of his fortification and its defenders.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, he increases the Siege Bonus of any fortification he defends by +1.</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase this bonus by an additional +1 for success and +2 with a raise by studying and better defending weak areas.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HJtbH3ZeMXNqHHnA"}
{"name":"Aristocrat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}&nbsp;Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the GM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his GM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the GM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. GMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HKAWYLMfEQOlQzjx"}
{"name":"Immortalized in Song","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>1</p>\n<p>Whether a brave warrior, a noble lord, or a powerful spellcaster, the character&rsquo;s place in history is assured for eternity. Songs are sung and poems told about his legendary deeds, parents name their children after the hero, and he is welcomed at any goodly settlement. When he eventually dies, he is guaranteed a burial befitting the greatest of heroes.</p>\n<p>The number of Followers the hero currently has doubles, as men flock to bask in his glory (this cannot be applied to Followers gained later). He may also take another Novice @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick} immediately.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic Status taken 4 times"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HLBzy9hYZBNjDLAR"}
{"name":"Natural Swimmer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your hero wasn't literally born in the water, but some might believe he was. He takes to it like a fish and can hold his breath longer than most others. Natural swimmers add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll for Swimmings, add +1 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} swimming, and can hold their breath 50% longer than others of their species.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HPMA1fiuj8nXw21m"}
{"name":"Oversized Weapon Master","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two-handed} melee weapons with one hand. He may only use one such weapon at a time, even if he has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Two-Fisted]{Two-Fisted} Edges, though he may use an oversize weapon in this manner and wield a standard one-handed weapon simultaneously.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d10+, Fighting d10+, Size 0 or greater"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HhMu2Mh40WRYCsyk"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Psionics)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, a character gains one die type in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HimnNrN3S3Qoimxw"}
{"name":"Mystic Theurge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Mystic theurges place no boundaries on their magical abilities, whether they stem from the arcane or divine.</p>\n<p><strong>Combined Spells: </strong>Much like the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} Edge, a theurge can cast two spells as one action, once per turn. The theurge must use two different arcane skills, declare her spells and all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers} as usual, then roll a die for each (the Wild Die can replace either). If the arcane skills have the same die type use different colored dice so you know which is which.</p>\n<p>The cost of both spells must be paid separately, and effects from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} apply normally but don&rsquo;t stack.</p>\n<h2 class=\"blue-example\">Example</h2>\n<p>A theurge casts <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em> with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} (d8) and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} (d10). She rolls a d8, a d10, and her Wild die, which may take the place of either skill die. She casts both spells, spends the usual number of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, and may use any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers} she wishes for each.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, two Arcane Backgrounds with two different arcane skills"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HmHg3eYiHbOfHWox"}
{"name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IF5KxBXuOt65EDG5"}
