{"name":"Sorcerer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Scions of magical bloodlines, pawns of fate and destiny, or simply flukes of fickle magic, sorcerers look within themselves for arcane prowess. As they tap into powers few mortals can imagine, these magic-touched souls must learn to harness the power of their birthright. While some seek to control their abilities, others give in to their magic, letting it rule their lives&mdash;often with explosive results.</p>\n<p>Sorcerers live and breathe that which other spellcasters devote their lives to mastering. For them magic is more than a useful tool or a field of study; it is life itself.</p>\n<p>Sorcerers have the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bloodline]{Bloodline}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cna61w56xkj","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Sorcerer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"M8QGeYW8uL1WDtYb"}
{"name":"Sneak Attack","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Rogue"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MJJjpNhMfPOgWlBB"}
{"name":"Sharp Tongued","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bards may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} a foe. They may also ignore the Repetition advice given under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as long as they recite different verses, stanzas, lyrics, etc. Bards may also substitute @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} to meet Edge Requirements.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MPAPtDI6eMxKrzpe"}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Paladin)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the paladin can invoke one of the following miracles: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>.&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em> are self only, but the paladin gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The paladin has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background. If the paladin also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Paladin"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MVRLVCTP6y6QDnd7"}
