{"name":"Quarry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The ranger's expertise expands to include additional enemies and terrain. Choose an additional enemy and terrain type for your @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Enemy]{Favored Enemy} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Terrain]{Favored Terrain}&nbsp;abilities.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken once per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Ranger"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y4rfdvvjk7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Ranger","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MxhMBaUt3KhbFVXi"}
{"name":"Opportunist","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When a target @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdraws from Melee} with the rogue, she gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} even if the foe has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Extraction]{Extraction} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Extraction]{Improved Extraction}. If the foe doesn&rsquo;t have either of those Edges, he counts as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to her for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Rogue"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N39glmWeFypdsZ3L"}
{"name":"Smite Evil (or Good)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}, a paladin can choose an enemy. If that enemy is evil (or good), she gets a free reroll on any failed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls against that target for the remainder of the encounter. She may use this ability once per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} per encounter.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Paladin"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N9HTxRs23k0idzQ2"}
{"name":"Arcane Armor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your Armor Interference counts as one level higher (so a character with Arcane Interference (Cloth) could wear Light armor with no penalty).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Armor Interference"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qafe4ipyce","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OH1yjxhL66e4Kbdv"}
{"name":"Steal Away","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero uses distraction and cover to slip away from his foes.</p>\n<p>The character may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid attack when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing from Melee]{Withdrawing} from close combat. He suffers a -1 penalty for each adjacent foe. Failure means foes may attack as normal as the adventurer withdraws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OYEl4i0fek5TQFOa"}
{"name":"Takedown Move","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When the hero successfully @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Pushes} an opponent, the opponent must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll at -2 (-4 if the hero got a raise) or be knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p>The wrestler can also chose not to push the opponent 1\" away, but just @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wrestler"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OxnR26hhfa7hszps"}
{"name":"Disciple of Onatar","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PM8eMu4w4k3fUaCS"}
{"name":"Mount","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero gains a light or heavy horse (trained in combat), or similar sized mount of Size 3 or less. The creature is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} and has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.Loyal]{Loyal} Hindrance (to its master only).</p>\n<p>When its master @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advances}, it may increase any one of its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Traits} (no more than once per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait}) or gain an Edge suitable for its type (GM's call); it must meet the Requirements as usual.</p>\n<p>If the mount perishes, the champion gains another in some way anytime after her next @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advance}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Paladin"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Pn11XBLpNdKzEvUE"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Druid)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q1EmKs08YC0EJ96t"}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Ranger)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the ranger can cast one of the following spells: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em>. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em> and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{warrior's gift}</em> are self only, but the ranger gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The woodsman has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.&nbsp; He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the ranger also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Ranger"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y4rfdvvjk7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Ranger","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q6yLSwMuFwnED1XZ"}
{"name":"Blind Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Blind fighters have trained long and hard to fight with out being able to see, using smell, sound, disturbances in the surrounding air, etc. You character is able to halves any penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}.</p>\n<p>Note this edge does not allow you to see in the dark only to fight at a reduced penalty when you vision is impaired.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Legnds of Steel</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Notice d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q9eWKiFj0dzdaglN"}
{"name":"Mark of Shadow","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Darkness}</em> (including True Darkness), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em> (including Duration), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Scrying]{scrying}</em>.&nbsp;</span><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise} </em>and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{intangibility}</em><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"> are </span>self only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.&nbsp; She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>The Mark of Shadow doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with the Mark of Shadow (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Elf"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m9rojhhzc3m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QGctzVxX2T5596dW"}
{"name":"Sucker Punch","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character doesn't know the meaning of the words \"fair fight.\" If he succeeds in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} against an adjacent opponent, the character receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack}. This attack does not incur a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action penalty}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, First Strike, Agility d6+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QWEfGQpDwMKvYVqH"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Artificer)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QhG63EYUhOtaz3ph"}
{"name":"Heroic Status","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>4</p>\n<p>This bonus represents how well known the hero is across Khorvaire. With heroes few and far between in the modern era, those who stand out from the crowd are widely recognized for their notable deeds.</p>\n<p>Common folk recognize the hero for his brave deeds and are likely to help him in his endeavors, if only for the bragging rights.</p>\n<p>He gains a +1 bonus to initial rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} when dealing with civilized races with whom he has a generally positive reputation, and to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} rolls each time he receives this perk, to a maximum of +4. This stacks with bonuses from any Professional Edges.</p>\n<p>A hero also gains the same bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls&mdash;enemies quake at his name and even allies are fearful of the character&rsquo;s prowess.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"20+ Glory"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QlEavIL1Wzbq4a3J"}
{"name":"Help Me!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a foe moves adjacent to the hero, the threatened character may call for help. One ally within the character&rsquo;s command radius who has not yet acted this turn may try to interrupt as if he were on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold}. With a success, the ally must attack the opponent who triggered this Edge.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QqZ4H2um3PjL4jqK"}
{"name":"Countersong","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The bard and all allies within 5&rdquo; (10 yards) get a free reroll when opposing enemy spell effects or attempting to recover from them. This includes rolls to recover from any magical effect such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{blind}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{lower Trait}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{stun}</em>. Countersong doesn&rsquo;t help targets resist or recover from natural effects.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Bard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Qv2ttmR5H8V2rGIZ"}
{"name":"True Hero","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When lesser men fall by the wayside, this hero just keeps soldiering on.</p>\n<p>When the character takes enough wounds to make him Incapacitated, he may make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll. Should the roll fail, the hero may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll as normal. If a character suffers multiple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} in the same round that take him to Incapacitated, he may make multiple free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Fafhrd already has 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds}, when two vicious wolves sink their teeth into him, inflicting 2 and 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} respectively. Fafhrd may make two free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls, one against each attack.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"R3wMaFQoUxdtdy3A"}
{"name":"Duelist II","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Duelist"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RAeCAZFpuRF9GFf5"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Six","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RNS2vw0wA4ycFrsr"}
{"name":"Wrestler","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero is trained in holds, locks, and takedowns. She may roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. She may also roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Crushing}. If she already has a damage die from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Claws}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edges, etc., increase the damage die by one type instead.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RfxfI2nOYEQKBpna"}
{"name":"Extreme Explorer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Survival d6+, Arcana or Common Knowledge d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RsVLMybuZlLFBx96"}
{"name":"Dragon Disciple","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Spellcasters who embrace their draconic heritage and learn to channel their abilities become fearsome warriors. They possess not only the repertoire of an accomplished sorcerer, but also the ability to unleash the furious power of dragons upon their foes.</p>\n<p><strong>Breath Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, the dragon disciple may use an action to make a breath attack in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Cone Template}. The attack causes 3d6 damage and may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}.</p>\n<p>The attack has one of the following effects, based on the type of dragon the character descends from: fire (victims may catch @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire}, page 156), acid (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Lingering Damage (+2)]{lingering} damage, see page 172), electricity (+2 damage to those in metal armor), or cold (victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hinder or Hurry (+1)]{hindered} until the end of his next turn, see page 172).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SQJ60qI3IZNgD0Ob"}
{"name":"Cry Havoc!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The general has an uncanny knack for knowing when to unleash his troops and when to hold back.</p>\n<p>Once per battle, during the Battle Roll Phase, the character may declare a charge. He must do this before he or his opponent rolls their Battle die. If the character succeeds in his roll and beats his opponent, his enemy loses one extra token.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Fervor, Spirit d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SYBOPeq6ZJ6hhLvO"}
{"name":"Code of Honor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>All paladins have the Code of Honor Hindrance, even evil ones though it might be different.</p>\n<p>Honor is very important to your character. He keeps his word, doesn&rsquo;t abuse or kill prisoners, and generally tries to operate within his world&rsquo;s particular notion of proper gentlemanly or ladylike behavior.</p>\n<p>This is in addition to their other Hindrances.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SfqhaOqFtMWboMrq"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Mockery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SsiOwsWue9Eiy8cy"}
{"name":"Duelist","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Duelists represent the pinnacle of elegant swordplay, parrying blows and countering their opponent&rsquo;s actions with expert ripostes.</p>\n<p><strong>Surgical Strike:</strong> The duelist makes a surgical strike with a one-handed piercing weapon with a Min Str of d6 or less, adding +2 to her damage total.</p>\n<p><strong>Parry:</strong> If the duelist hasn&rsquo;t acted this turn, she may declare the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Defend]{Defend} maneuver after an opponent declares a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against her but before he rolls. She discards her current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} and her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} bonus is +6 instead of +4 that turn.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"StlVQhmwMtOlhkIB"}
{"name":"Favored","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>2</p>\n<p>The adage that there are old heroes and bold heroes, but no old, bold heroes doesn&rsquo;t apply to this character.</p>\n<p>Whether because he believes in his own legend and refuses to get up when the going gets tough, or whether the gods are smiling on him, the hero can do things other heroes can&rsquo;t.</p>\n<p>He gains a free benny. This adds to his regular total, thus increasing the number he starts each session with.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"60+ Glory"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"T8x2s9HjJNF9Y52V"}
{"name":"Nature Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Nature rewards its defenders with additional power and energy to power their miracles. A druid who takes this Edge gains access to all her powers&rsquo; Epic Power Modifiers .</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Druid"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UFASKbpVnbsHeRFe"}
{"name":"Assassin II","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Assassin"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V3U4Auo99Qozr2Sm"}
{"name":"Arcane Archer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>An arcane archer uses magical energies to amplify his arrows or bolts. He may automatically grant one \"quality\" into any arrow he fires (designated per shot).</p>\n<p>The first two qualities an archer learns are:</p>\n<p><strong>Enhance:</strong> The archer's arrow adds +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} and damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Trapping:</strong> The arrow has an environmental Trapping such as fire, cold, darkness, etc.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WQ0GngG937omHIHY"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Ancestors","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wtnuykszdmc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WgOsdmoEWcy2GReo"}
{"name":"Improved Martial Flexibility","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The fighter gains the benefits of two Combat Edges per encounter (subject to the usual restrictions of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Flexibility]{Martial Flexibility}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Fighter"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cbe5u35c01","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Fighter","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XypvWRo4PHptMw0t"}
{"name":"Arcane Trickster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>These prodigious thieves blend subtle aspects of the arcane with the cunning of sleight of hand and misdirection.</p>\n<p><strong>Ranged Legerdemain:</strong> The trickster can use his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} at a Range of 5&rdquo; (10 yards) or less at a &minus;2 penalty. Any object manipulated at range must weigh less than 5 pounds.</p>\n<p><strong>Impromptu Attack:</strong> Once per encounter, the trickster may use her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack} ability even if a foe isn&rsquo;t @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or subject to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any), Sneak Attack ability, Thievery d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Y2khy5AJ3035E5Uo"}
{"name":"Dirge of Doom","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This baleful song builds dread in the bard&rsquo;s foes. At his discretion, any enemy who spends a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} or reroll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or damage roll within 10&rdquo; (20 yards) and line of sight of the bard subtracts 2 from the final total.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Bard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YSsvMQ7IyOMBLuNu"}
{"name":"Powerful Blow","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The barbarians&rsquo; savage @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{wild attacks} cause +4 damage instead of +2.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Barbarian"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_uz53jzntey","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Barbarian","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YcNfsaz0U9iqH0Lw"}
{"name":"Favored Powers (Artificer)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer has great familiarity with certain powers and can cast them quickly and easily. Once per turn, he may ignore up to two points of any penalties (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, etc.) when casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item},&nbsp;</em><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em><em>, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em>.</p>\n<p>This Edge doesn&rsquo;t give him those powers&mdash; they must be taken separately.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZhM4oJhqCJSCYq4H"}
{"name":"Sidekick","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>1</p>\n<p>Regardless of his character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}, the hero has attracted a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}, as per the Edge. If the Sidekick dies, the character may take this benefit again when he earns more Glory. A second Sidekick may be gained at Legendary as normal through taking the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick} Edge with an advance.</p>\n<p>Like Followers, Sidekicks remain with the hero when his Glory drops, but may grumble, not perform to the best of their abilities, or even refuse to follow orders. When the Glory rises sufficiently high again, the Sidekick returns to his former loyal state.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"80+ Glory"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xbof4ishapq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZtazcsnAXAwYxlyY"}
{"name":"Stunning Fist","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When a monk hits a target with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unarmed Strike]{Unarmed Strike} and scores a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he may make the foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}. This occurs even if the victim takes no damage or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soaks} it (the states are applied after the victim attempts to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Monk"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7kugpblr0yu","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Monk","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aDOPVbkVhLAgQMQC"}
