{"name":"Rich","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he&rsquo;s got more money than most.</p>\n<p>Rich heroes start with 900 gold galifars instead of the usual 300. The hero also receives (1d6+6) x 100 gp per week, perhaps from family holdings, a profitable business, or an inheritance. Whether he can get to it or not is another matter. It might simply build up in an account, or more likely, as a collection of assets such as a manor or estate. Of course that kind of wealth usually comes with obligations to spend it, pay taxes, or take care of retainers, employees, caretakers, and grounds.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_phrvgu41m1d","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"alj6RBWSaQdWoqMY"}
