{"name":"Finely  Tuned","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer has studied under the best masters in his field and has fine tuned his creations to maximum efficiency.</p>\n<p>When creating an <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Device}</strong>, each raise an artificer gets on his activation roll reduces the cost of the power by 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}, to a minimum of 1. The Arcane Device must have the full points available to use the power in the first place before rolling. You only need to take this Edge once, not for each Arcane Device.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer, Smarts d8+, Crafting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qafe4ipyce","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fNBhVu7OxrL1eZUC"}
{"name":"Dragon Disciple II","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dragon Disciple"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fQSfJ1JgaTvXnLLp"}
{"name":"Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In Eberron, magic is almost technology. Spellcasters specialize in certain forms of that technology, while artificers tinker with its fundamental workings. Artificers understand magic on a different level from spellcasters, and do not cast spells as wizards and clerics do. They have an amazing facility with magic items and constructs, and in many ways, they keep the magical world of Eberron running.</p>\n<p>Masters of unlocking magic in everyday objects, artificers are supreme inventors. They see magic as a complex system waiting to be decoded and controlled. Artificers use tools to channel arcane power, crafting magical objects. To cast a spell, an artificer could use alchemist's supplies to create a potent elixir, calligrapher's supplies to inscribe a sigil of power on an ally's armor, or tinker's tools to craft a temporary charm. The magic of artificers is tied to their tools and their talents.</p>\n<p>Artificers gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Artificer)]{Arcane Background (Artificer)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant Magic Item]{Enchant Magic Item}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Homunculus]{Homunculus}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Infuse Item]{Infuse Item}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fRrPYoNajhHOWHHF"}
{"name":"Schools","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A wizard&rsquo;s intense studies lead him down two paths&mdash;a &ldquo;universalist&rdquo; who dabbles in all the various &ldquo;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools}&rdquo; of magic, or a &ldquo;specialist&rdquo; who focuses on one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school}&nbsp;at the expense of some others.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Specialists</strong></em> designate one favored @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school} and two opposition @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools} from the list below. They gain one free reroll when casting spells from their favored @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school}, but spells cast from their opposition @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school} cost one additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} and suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} penalty.</p>\n<p>Opposition spells should be marked with an asterisk in a character&rsquo;s power lists, like this: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{banish}*</em>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Universalists</strong></em> have no favored or opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools}, and thus gain none of the advantages or disadvantages of specialists.</p>\n<p>Here are the various schools</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gBwLqDlgaVSR34Yg"}
{"name":"Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal.</p>\n<p>Close fighters move inside most weapons' reach, adding a bonus to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy weapon's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1 for that particular foe. No bonus is granted if the foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{unarmed} or using a knife or other small weapon.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Lhazaar pirate with Close Fighting battles a Lyrandar heir with a cutlass ( @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 0 ). The pirates @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} is raised by +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gHxvh2AdXy272IxB"}
{"name":"Fast","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Barbarians are fast and durable runners. They increase their base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} by +2. This doesn&rsquo;t affect their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die}, but does stack with Edges like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed} or racial modifiers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Barbarian"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_uz53jzntey","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Barbarian","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"suEcQ6e8TEBqE58I","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","value":2,"mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/run.svg","label":"Fast","tint":"","transfer":true}],"_id":"gak9gGVdA0XicfSw"}
{"name":"Vow of Faith","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Clerics have a major vow to serve their deity. Those who wish to draw energy from divine sources must uphold the principles of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Domains]{Domains}.</p>\n<p>If the cleric violates their deity's trust (DM's call) the cleric subtracts 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rzst3tdjv7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Cleric","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gcVKKuPQHv8Zdjq8"}
{"name":"Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Like sorcerers, wizards must gesticulate in precise patterns. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} rolls&nbsp;and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls&nbsp;when wearing light, medium, or heavy armor, or using light, medium, or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hThTtTmXl1h09a69"}
{"name":"Uncanny Reflexes","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The rogue has an uncanny ability to avoid area attacks and effects. She ignores the usual &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} penalty when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} attempts. She also gets a regular @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} attempt against area effect attacks or effects that don&rsquo;t usually allow it (at the usual &minus;2 penalty) such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{burst}</em> or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>, or even <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em> or similar spells cast with the Area Effect modifier.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Rogue"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fnvf8cdvngc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Rogue","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hYsXNrmhaK041pf0"}
{"name":"Favored Enemy","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rangers study their foes, learning their ways, how to find them, and how to defeat them. Choose a type of enemy (Aberration, Animal, Construct, Dragon, Elemental, Fey, Giant, Humanoid (two), Monstrosity, Ooze, Outsider, Plant, Undead, or Vermin). The ranger gets one free reroll when failing to track (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival}) or attack (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) that type of being.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y4rfdvvjk7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Ranger","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hrQOJeqBjy5citxz"}
