{"name":"Coordinated Firepower","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to coordinate missile fire against a single foe.</p>\n<p>Instead of firing separately, all missile troops within the hero's command radius yet to act in the round can fire as a single unit on the hero's action (this counts as their entire action for the round).</p>\n<p>The hero nominates one foe within range of his weapon. He then makes a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, as appropriate for his weapon. Each additional missile soldier within the hero's command range (and within range of the target), firing at the same time adds a flat +2 to the attack roll.</p>\n<p>Damage is calculated as normal for the hero's weapon, but he adds +1d6 per raise (not just for the first raise). Coordinating fire in this manner counts as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{single action}.</p>\n<p>A hero cannot use Double Shot or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer} in conjunction with this Edge unless all subordinates firing with the hero have those Edges as well.</p>\n<p>Although the soldiers lose their individual attacks, the combined firepower gives a better chance of bringing down a large foe (like a dragon), and unlike separate missile fire, the entire damage roll is applied once against the foe's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Command, Smarts d6+, Athletics or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_13m4lijdpgi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oeFPsr0Pz9Rzll7P"}
{"name":"Inspire Heroics","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bards inspire their comrades with epic tales of valor and bravery. Once during any combat encounter (GM&rsquo;s call), the bard can spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to gain five Inspiration tokens. This is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</p>\n<p>For the remainder of the encounter, the bard may give these tokens to anyone within a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} except himself. This may be done at any time (as long as the bard is conscious). The recipient must use the token immediately&mdash;it cannot be saved.</p>\n<p>Each Inspiration token allows a character to reroll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or damage roll. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or damage roll may only benefit from a single Inspiration Token, even if there are multiple bards present. Further rerolls require spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}&nbsp;or a special ability.</p>\n<p>Inspiration tokens aren&rsquo;t @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}, don&rsquo;t trigger Edges that use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} (such as Elan), and can&rsquo;t be used as such in any other way such as drawing new @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} or Soaking Wounds.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ze2njv8yroq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Bard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"om0z4KACSuv6YN2B"}
{"name":"Arcane Trickster II","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Trickster"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ceovwsdga4w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Prestige Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oniLdlStzZnt0q0k"}
{"name":"Arcane Bond","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wizards form an intense magical bond with an object or creature.</p>\n<p>Wizards immerse themselves in the study of eldritch lore and arcane theories. During these long hours they form a bond with a dependable item or friendly creature (a &ldquo;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Familiar]{familiar}&rdquo;). Choose one of the following options for your wizard:</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Bonded Object: </strong>The spellcaster possesses an amulet, ring, staff, wand, or weapon that adds +1 to all his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} totals when worn or in hand. If the object is lost or destroyed, the mage can replace it with a new object worth at least 500 gp.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Familiar]{Familiar}:</strong> The mage has a magical pet.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6v947zso8xk","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Wizard","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"orqyltXVEQU5TTUh"}
{"name":"Artifice Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>True understanding of technology of magical energy comes with practice and experience. Artificers who take this Edge gain access to all their powers&rsquo; Epic Power Modifiers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Artificer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"p8DLj2zEUAI0kenY"}
{"name":"Paladin","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Through a worthy few shines the power of the divine. Called paladins, these noble souls dedicate their swords and lives to the battle against evil. Knights, crusaders, and lawbringers, paladins seek not just to spread righteous justice but to embody the teachings of the virtuous deities they serve. In pursuit of their lofty goals, they adhere to ironclad laws of morality and discipline.</p>\n<p>As a reward for their service, these holy champions are blessed with boons to aid them in their quests. They gain abilities to battle evil opponents, heal allies, and inspire the faithful. Their conviction leads them into conflict with the very souls they would save. Paladins weather endless challenges of faith and temptation. They risk their lives to do right and ensure justice.</p>\n<p>Paladins gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aura of Courage]{Aura of Courage}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Detect Evil (or Good)]{Detect Evil (or Good)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Smite Evil (or Good)]{Smite Evil (or Good)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Spirit d6+, Vow (Minor—serve their deity or order)"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_m959usuw6w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Paladin","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pHwgGD7KxUJJiz16"}
{"name":"Barbarian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>For some, there is only rage. In the ways of their people, in the fury of their passion, in the howl of battle, these brutal souls swear by the creed of conflict. Battle possessed, these savage warriors disdain the life of the professional guard or soldier. They seek to fight for the sake of the act itself.</p>\n<p>Known as barbarians, these warmongers know little of tactics, preparation, or the rules of warfare. For them, only the moment exists. They embrace the possibility that the next battle might hold their death. Within the barbarian&rsquo;s heart beats the primal spirit of struggle. Those who face their rage, beware.</p>\n<p>Barbarians gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast]{Fast}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rage]{Rage}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_uz53jzntey","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Barbarian","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"suEcQ6e8TEBqE58I","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","value":2,"mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/run.svg","label":"Fast","tint":"","transfer":true}],"_id":"pqS80RVtJA6XABnt"}
{"name":"Brutal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character with this @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{edge} is more dangerous when roughed up. When determining melee damage, he adds his wound level to the roll. A hero with 3 wounds, for instance, adds +3 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nyz86xwgjxi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pz0XkacL18lV8oy9"}
