{"name":"Cleric","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In faith and the miracles of the divine, many find a greater purpose. Called to serve powers beyond most mortal understanding, all priests provide for the spiritual needs of their people. More than mere preachers, clerics serve as emissaries of their gods. These ecclesiastics vow to spread the tenets, knowledge, and truth of their faith.</p>\n<p>While clerics of different faiths may share similar abilities, they prove as different from one another as the divinities they serve. Some offer healing and redemption, others judge law and truth, and still others spread conflict and corruption.</p>\n<p>Clerics gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Vow of Faith]{Vow of Faith}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Faith d4+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rzst3tdjv7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Cleric","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yM0icO6krseyfJ5U"}
{"name":"Nature Bond","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A druid may attune herself to nature or a special animal companion.</p>\n<p>The bonds druids form with nature are deep and powerful. Choose one of these abilities:</p>\n<p><strong>Attuned:</strong> The druid gets one free reroll anytime she fails a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} roll to activate a spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Beast Master:</strong> The druid gains the Beast Master Edge, and her companion automatically starts as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0j1u3hopqpse","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Druid","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"z8JCQphNGxDuFb5d"}
{"name":"Enchant Magic Item","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Artificers can imbue their powers into @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane devices} for later use or give them to their allies. This ties up their own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, however, and such creations are temporary.</p>\n<p>With enough time and resources, however, an artificer can create more permanent items of wonder, and best of all he doesn&rsquo;t have to tie up his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} in the process!</p>\n<p>They can follow the rules for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Crafting Magic Items]{crafting magic items} with the benefit of making progress at a rate of 600 gp on a success, or 1,200 gp with a raise.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Artificer"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_58ynsuma4xq","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Class Edges#/CF_SEP/Artificer","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zBzJEzvJVhW7mK58"}
