{"name":"Assassin","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+, Stealth d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XHXECEu46qxTYlbw"}
{"name":"Born in the Saddle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Whether it&rsquo;s on the back of fast horse or other more exotic mount, this hero feels more at home in the saddle than on her own two feet.</p>\n<p>The Edge grants the hero one free reroll on all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} rolls and increases her mount&rsquo;s Pace by 2 and its running die one step.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Riding d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Befldow4EGYr4aQu"}
{"name":"Entertainer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You character is skilled in ther performing arts: singing, story telling, comedy, acting, slieght of hand, etc. They also adept in speaking before a crowd.</p>\n<p>Pick any two of the following skills: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} and add +1 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iY9WYjbMCcRIwUTP"}
{"name":"Holy Adept","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Adepts are holy warriors who have trained themselves to be living weapons. Some do so to be ultimate warriors; others do it in the service of a cause or deity.</p>\n<p>Their unarmed attacks do @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 damage, and they are always considered armed for purposes of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender} rule.</p>\n<p>In addition, upon taking this Edge and at each new Rank, they may choose to add the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{limitation} of Self to one of the following powers but be activated as a free action: <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em>, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Healing]{healing}</em>, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>. The Adept must have the power to begin with, and this does not allow him to activate more than one power in a round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Cleric or Divine Magic), Faith d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uy6IyV6QsFyNTP2N"}
{"name":"Inquisitive","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Investigators spend a great deal of time researching ancient legends, working the streets, or deducing devilish mysteries. Some of these heroes are actual inquiisitives while others are sleuthing mages in a fantasy world or inquisitive college professors stumbling upon Things Man Was Not Meant to Know.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Investigators add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Lore]{Lore} rolls and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made to search through desks for important papers, sift through stacks of junk mail for something of note, or spy obscured items from piles of junk or debris</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Lore d8+"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Kscb09iroKn4Caho"}
{"name":"Knight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Knights are chivalric heroes dedicated to a particular cause. All Knights swear holy oaths to their patron, whether it is a god, an order, or a noble, and must answer the call when summoned&mdash;even if it means his certain death.</p>\n<p>Upon acceptance into his order, a knight is gifted with the tools of his trade&mdash;a light warhorse, a lance, chain mail armor, and a medium shield emblazoned with the symbol of his patron.</p>\n<p>In addition to these material rewards, Knights of good causes gain +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LqY9T1g8ccBQoTW2"}
{"name":"Legendary Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The party gains +1d8 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory} for each raise after the first when using the Variable Glory Awards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Master Storyteller"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AYxusb3js8ntnpDm"}
{"name":"Master Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Zombies raised by the Necromancer now have an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice (usually @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Necromancer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vZqtGBjWKUMwX7QB"}
{"name":"Master Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Tales of brave heroes and epic battles are told across Khorvaire in taverns and around hearths and campfires. Most master storytellers are skalds or bards.</p>\n<p>When using the Variable @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory}&nbsp;Awards rules (p. 100), the characters roll d8s instead of a d6s if this hero recounts their deeds.</p>\n<p>In addition, the storyteller is adept at deflecting bad press through carefully chosen words. The party suffers no penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory}&nbsp;if the storyteller rolls a critical failure, treating it as a regular failure.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source; Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uF6MpHLLlJPY2kKH"}
{"name":"Monster Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character is completely immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks from one broad type of creature, such as ghosts, werewolves, vampires, or constructs. If applied to spellcasters, it includes the fear spell as well.</p>\n<p>The Game Master is the final arbiter of whether or not the Edge applies to a particular horror.</p>\n<p>The Edge may be taken multiple times, each applying to a different creature type.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ir8eDWejlfZ3DEdx"}
{"name":"Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p>\n<p>The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} power at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice} level (rather than its normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran} Rank requirement).</p>\n<p>Second, when casting zombie , the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p>\n<p>A Necromancer may never have more than twice his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die in permanent undead servants.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rhevUCXVLfNsUGBi"}
{"name":"Rope Monkey","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rope Monkeys are those sailors who may as well have been born in the rigging. They always seem to know just the right rope to cut and pull to swing to some other part of the ship and can ride the lines down to avoid an otherwise nasty fall.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkey has two functions. The first is to allow a character on the exterior of the ship to move to any other exposed part of the ship by swinging from the rigging. This counts as the character&rsquo;s movement and requires a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll. If successful, he moves to any other external area of the ship. He may not move further this action even by \"running.\" With a raise, he can move and gains momentary surprise on any foes, adding +2 to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks and damage rolls for the round. This can also be combined with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} maneuver.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also use this ability in forests with tall trees. In that case, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll is made at &minus;2 and the character may reposition himself within d10\".</p>\n<p>A foe who wants to take his free attack at a Rope Monkey swinging out of melee must subtract 2 from his roll. The same applies to characters with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}&mdash;they suffer a &minus;2 penalty to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll any time they fall from a ship&rsquo;s rigging (and are conscious). Success means they take half the usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling} damage by grabbing onto ropes as they tumble. With a raise, the sailor manages to slide down a rope and suffers no damage.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LrPCtpX3UsPnFFSs"}
{"name":"Troubadour","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Troubadours travel the world, learning culture, etiquette, history, and above all, legends. They add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls and may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} in place of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} for Leadership @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges} that require @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Common Knowledge d6+, Performance d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZEu3IFoVEA3uMbQa"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ywlbf12gp4m","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000","name":"Professional Edges","children":["XHXECEu46qxTYlbw","Befldow4EGYr4aQu","iY9WYjbMCcRIwUTP","uy6IyV6QsFyNTP2N","Kscb09iroKn4Caho","LqY9T1g8ccBQoTW2","AYxusb3js8ntnpDm","vZqtGBjWKUMwX7QB","uF6MpHLLlJPY2kKH","ir8eDWejlfZ3DEdx","rhevUCXVLfNsUGBi","LrPCtpX3UsPnFFSs","ZEu3IFoVEA3uMbQa"],"folderPath":["temp_eh5365j3hoj"]}},"effects":[],"_id":"0KfIeblwCSjmTx9K"}
{"name":"Adamantine Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged was created from a specially designed line made with adamantine giving him +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}&nbsp;instead of the normal +2 from Composite Plating.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uJNMajeZJ0wbCYYc"}
{"name":"Bladedancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bladedancers are elite elven warriors, this Edge is their trademark combat maneuver. Despite the name, they may use weapons.</p>\n<p>When used, an elf spins and dances about, attacking every opponent in his path like a deadly cyclone. On the tabletop, the character makes a running roll and must move that many inches. He may not double back.</p>\n<p>Every target adjacent to the fighter's path, starting with his initial position, is attacked at &minus;2. One small downside to this Edge is that every adjacent target must be attacked&mdash;whether friend or foe. Individual targets may only be attacked once while using this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Elf, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+, Two-Fisted"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZNrcIHoZLprLquta"}
{"name":"Extra Shifter Ability","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer come from a mixed lineage of shifters and has one additional shifter ability. They can manifest this additional ability while shifted as well.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"k4nUVyfupE124Odu"}
{"name":"Fighting Withdrawl","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero can defend himself even while running away. The character may run while using the Defend maneuver.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Agility, Fighting d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"adXRTBnkcrsRnyJn"}
{"name":"Healing Factor","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>After the shifter's current period of shifting ends, she may immediately make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll to remove any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wounds} taken while shifted.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shifter (any), Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aemOnf7bOaDItT5M"}
{"name":"Improved Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With sufficient willpower, a hero who has learned to trigger his rage can restrain it as well. Improved Primal Fury allows the hero to ignore the &minus;2 penalty to end his rage, and on a Critical Failure, he will not hit an ally while @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} (though he may still hit the wrong opponent or miss).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Primal Fury, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9rrXMSjZJgi0fIxF"}
{"name":"Improved Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The halfling can move so quickly as to cause multiple opponents to interfere with each other's attacks. Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Ganging Up} bonus against the halfling.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Scamper"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rP7zstOrweQmjN2R"}
{"name":"Improved Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 2 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sunder"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PF9xK22yV5juZYyQ"}
{"name":"Overload Metabolism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged can heal damage at a cost to his other physical attributes by exciting his warforged metabolism. Once per session, he can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair damage. On a success, he repairs one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}. On a raise, he repairs two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wounds}. Doing this reduces his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} by one die type for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>If the warforged is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Incapacitated} and has not yet used this ability, any use of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]{Imbue Item} Edge targeted upon him automatically activates this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Agility d8+, Strength d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oDNDicI9CDkrm9hG"}
{"name":"Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some half-orcs or orcs have an animal rage inside them they can trigger consciously. A half-orc or orc with Prinal Fury may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Half-orc or Orc, Berserk"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XGlxPKTyhrhF79xz"}
{"name":"Psicrystal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A psicrystal is a fragment of a kalashtar's personality, brought into physical form and a semblance of life. It appears as a crystalline construct about the size of a human hand.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Personalities: </strong>A psicrystal has its own personality (a fragment of the owner's personality), which gives its owner a bonus on certain types of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as given on the table below. These special abilities and bonuses apply only when the owner and the psicrystal are within 1 mile of each other.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Bully:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} checks</li>\n<li><em>Friendly: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks</li>\n<li><em>Hero:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Nimble:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} rolls to interrupt actions</li>\n<li><em>Observant: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} checks</li>\n<li><em>Resolved:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Sage:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} checks</li>\n<li><em>Single-minded: </em>+1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls while maintaining powers</li>\n<li><em>Sneaky: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} checks</li>\n<li><em>Sympathetic: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smart} rolls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each psicrystal has a distinct personality, chosen by its owner at the time of its creation from among those given on the table. Upon taking this Edge, its owner typically gets a feel for a psicrystal's personality only through occasional impulses, but as the owner increases gains experience, the psicrystal's personality becomes more pronounced.</p>\n<p>As the owner advances, it is not uncommon for a psicrystal to constantly ply its owner with observations and advice, often severely slanted toward the psicrystal's particular worldview. The owner always sees a bit of himself in his psicrystal, even if magnified and therefore distorted.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Advancement:</strong> At each Rank of the owner, the psicrystal has the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Novice:</em> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] +1; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d4</li>\n<li><em>Seasoned: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+2; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d6</li>\n<li><em>Veteran: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+3; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d8</li>\n<li><em>Heroic: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+4; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d10</li>\n<li><em>Legendary: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+5; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d12</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A psicrystal can speak one language of its owner's choice (so long as it is a language the owner knows). A psicrystal can understand all other languages known by its owner, but cannot speak them.</p>\n<p>Because of the telepathic link between a psicrystal and its owner, the owner has the same connection to an item or place that the psicrystal does. For instance, if his psicrystal has seen a room, the owner can teleport into that room as if he has seen it too, negating the -4 penalty for the destination being an unknown area; the -2 penalty for not being able to see it presently might still apply.</p>\n<p>The psicrystal is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} with respect to Wounds and the Wild Die, but has no Prophecy Shards. The owner may spend his for the psicrystal, however.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the psion can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The psion may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the psion to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The psicrystal gains @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} against psionics.</li>\n<li>The psion can transfer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} levels to or from his psicrystal as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free actions}.</li>\n<li>The psion can use the psicrystal's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the psion's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>Whenever the psicrystal is adjacent to or in the possession of its owner, the owner has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Alertness]{Alertness} Edge.</li>\n<li>Any powers the psion manifests on himself also affect the psicrystal. If he manifests armor with a raise, both he and his psicrystal gain +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The psicrystal has 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, which the psion may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the psion's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n<li>The psicrystal can act as a conduit for the psion's powers by delivering touch powers manifested by its owner. The owner and the psicrystal must be in contact at the time the power is manifested. The power must be delivered before the owner can manifest another power. At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Legendary} Rank, the owner can manifest the power through the psicrystal to a distance of up to 1 mile.</li>\n<li>At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Seasoned} Rank or above, the owner, as a standard action, can will his psicrystal to fly with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6. The effect lasts for one day (or until the owner dismisses it, at which point the psicrystal drifts gently to the ground).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the psicrystal is destroyed, the character must take this Edge again to create a new psicrystal. However, the previous acquisitions of this Edge to add to its abilities are applied to the new psicrystal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Kalashtar, Arcane Background (Psionics), Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"C75UQ162Gjjav3cm"}
{"name":"Psiforged Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This warforged's body has trace amounts of psionically resonant deep crystal, providing her with increased psionic power and the ability to store psionic energy in its body. This functions as a mana stone (see Named Miscellaneous Magic in the Fantasy Companion) with 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}. A warforged with this edge is sometimes referred to as a psiforged.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0uJoUyX5YSUT5hL3"}
{"name":"Reactive Shifting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can activate their abilities as a reflex. Reactive Shifting allows them to begin shifting as a free action even when it's not their turn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any), Quick"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OBMFeAeDuYCrK9xt"}
{"name":"Running Throw","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to use his momentum to boost the range of thrown weapons.</p>\n<p>If the character moves at least half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} immediately before making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to throw a weapon he increases the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} of his thrown weapon by 2/4/8. No other actions may be performed between moving and throwing, and the two maneuvers must be taken in the same round.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Strength d8, Athletics d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5KpV4l7DsZ1ELJcg"}
{"name":"Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Halflings are small and quick. Some make great use of this in combat too, scampering about to avoid the blows of larger foes. Opponents of man-size or larger subtract 1 from attack rolls against halflings with this Edge. The benefit only applies when the character is aware the attack is coming, he is unbound and able to move freely, and has no encumbrance penalty.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Halfling, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qSVWuQbju5xYoBqk"}
{"name":"Shieldwall","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge allows a hero to defend a comrade so long as the hero is using a medium or large shield.</p>\n<p>Attacks against one character adjacent to the hero suffer modifiers based on the hero's shield type. If there are multiple heroes with this Edge adjacent to a character or the target has his own shield, only the best modifier applies. A hero adjacent to multiple allies must declare which one he is protecting at the start of his turn.</p>\n<p>The hero also keeps his shield modifier if he is attacked.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Hobgoblin, Block"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pM74Wtkv6LIRxsbL"}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal damage}, and the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2UVOEB6b1KHCP6rd"}
{"name":"Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dwarf"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3WEsEogLeurOPRLd"}
{"name":"War Cry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bugbear, Half-orc, and Orc can bellow an ear-splitting, nervewracking war cry that has been known to send lesser foes fleeing from the field.</p>\n<p>When used, the character may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{test} against all targets in an area (as opposed to a single victim as usual). Place the edge of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} adjacent to the character. Every creature, friend and foe, within the circle must roll against the hero's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} total.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hly8u58ip0a","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"66Zn54wLAUD3pbUn"}
