{"name":"Storm Chaser","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When the weather is at its worst the character is at his best, seeming to read the storm like he would a book. Such characters are respected for their skill but feared for their love of a good storm.</p>\n<p>The character receives +1 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} rolls made during a storm. In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases} each round during a storm and keep the best card, as long as he is the Captain. If the character has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense} Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating or Piloting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_dhtqpt7kwrw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UWkTSf2nv5Eqlolb"}
{"name":"Symbiont Mastery","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer has stronger control over attached symbionts and benefits from increased vitality from the attached symbionts. She gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls during any battle of wills between her and the symbiont (see Intelligent Relics in Fantasy Companion). While at least one symbiont is attached, the adventurer also gains a free reroll on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_dhtqpt7kwrw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CGcuZDwpzwSTtTwd"}
{"name":"Wind Sense","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character has an almost supernatural knowledge of air and wind. He can sense changes in the weather and wind direction long before they actually happen.</p>\n<p>If the character is piloting a ship he gains +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} rolls during Contact, using his knowledge of the winds to outrun and catch prey.</p>\n<p>In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chase} each round during a storm and keeps the best as long as the Captain heeds his warnings. If the character has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]{Storm Chaser} Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Boating or Piloting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_dhtqpt7kwrw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xyHHfRlyqfRkMNqp"}
